Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.29,0:00:05.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Rhinoceros Hornbill, of the order\NCoraciiformes, family Bucerotidae.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.96,0:00:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This king of the rain forest is known\Nas the two-headed monster bird
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.09,0:00:16.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because of the giant horn on top of its beak.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.34,0:00:23.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until recently, the way it raised\Nits chicks was largely unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.85,0:00:27.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umpteen meters above the ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.56,0:00:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it buiIds a nest in the opening of a tree\Nby sealing the opening with grass and mud,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.86,0:00:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,leaving just enough room for the parent\Nbird to deliver the food it brings back.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.61,0:00:41.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inside this secluded environment is where\Nthe life of the Rhinoceros Hornbill begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.45,0:00:49.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The nest acts as a second egg for the chick that is growing\Nup inside and preparing for the day of departure.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.75,0:00:54.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is also a fortress that protects the chick\Nfrom predators such as apes and raptors.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.47,0:00:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If anyone should approach this enclosed\Nworld without permission,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.34,0:01:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even the parent with food, it will be...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.40,0:01:13.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The parent announces its arrival by\Nmaking a unique flapping sound,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.28,0:01:16.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the chick responds with a chirp.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.15,0:01:20.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The need for rules between parent\Nand child applies not only to birds,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.83,0:01:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but also to humans,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.12,0:01:27.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as the case may be.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.71,0:01:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's an overprotected child,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.67,0:01:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she's a brat leading a sheltered life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.96,0:01:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unaware of the hard labor that their parents endure,\Nthey slack, laze, eat, sleep and repeat the above...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.55,0:01:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After an appropriate amount of time, even a seed\Nsprouts and eventually produces a flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.89,0:01:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Peaches and chestnuts take three years, persimmons eight,\Nand plums thirteen, despite the sourness of the fruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.56,0:01:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hardworking chick studies by the light\Nof snow outside and fireflies at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.11,0:01:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After many moons have come and gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.69,0:01:58.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when the food supply from the parents stops,\Nthe chick peeks out and shudders in horror.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.91,0:02:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The parents urge it to come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.54,0:02:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't think that parents and money last forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.08,0:02:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The body longs for the freedom of the-outside world,\Nand the mind longs for the peace of the enclosed world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.67,0:02:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is the ambivalence of adolescence.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.92,0:02:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To live or to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.92,0:02:19.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.93,0:02:22.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, now, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.56,0:02:32.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, it breaks the seal with its own hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.40,0:02:37.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and how does the world look to a young bird\Nstepping out into reality for the first time?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.54,0:02:58.96,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,I watch the sky through the keyhole, and\Nwhat I see is a person's silhouette
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.26,0:03:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(143, 175)}A Production by:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.26,0:03:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(170, 210)}Yuji Nunokawa
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.67,0:03:05.43,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my casual encounter with a tomorrow I've never seen
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.55,0:03:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(420, 325)}Producer:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.55,0:03:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(480,360)}Hiroshi Umezaki
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.93,0:03:11.23,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Outer space always starts from an interphone
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.39,0:03:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(460,155)}Character Design
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.39,0:03:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(460,180)}& Animation Director:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.39,0:03:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(485,215)}Satoru Utsunomiya
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.10,0:03:17.78,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, one step out, and I find the desert
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.40,0:03:20.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(190, 295)}Art Director:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.40,0:03:20.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(170, 325)}Yoji Ikeda
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.40,0:03:20.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(180,365)}Director of Photography:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.40,0:03:20.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(180,400)}Nobuo Koyama
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.28,0:03:23.78,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no armor to protect the family
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.45,0:03:31.12,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,The only weapon to search for our roots is consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.74,0:03:28.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(420, 140)}Music:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.74,0:03:28.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(460, 175)}Kenji Kawai
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.74,0:03:28.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(430, 210)}Sound Director:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.74,0:03:28.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(470, 245)}Shigeru Chiba
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.62,0:03:41.09,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,If only you had love, dreams, and frontiers...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.80,0:03:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(410, 295)}Editing:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.80,0:03:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(460, 330)}Seiji Morita
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.80,0:03:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(450, 370)}Opening Animation:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.80,0:03:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(455, 405)}Koji Nanke
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.01,0:03:52.81,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Lineage, the road home, heritage, and\Norigins depend on space and time
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.39,0:03:54.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(180, 170)}Original script & Screenplay\N& Director:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.39,0:03:54.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(170, 205)}Mamoru Oshii
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.35,0:04:01.15,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,The wife has the household, the servant, and the genealogy
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.32,0:04:06.28,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Transcend and run through the time
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.20,0:04:13.58,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Long long life to the ancestors!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.44,0:05:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shoplifters!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.10,0:05:18.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thieves!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.85,0:05:20.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yamada, call the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.24,0:05:25.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.96,0:05:41.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Klutz!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.96,0:05:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, great-grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.13,0:05:47.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not safe around here anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.22,0:05:49.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd better move to another city soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.47,0:05:51.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's getting dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.55,0:05:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sure hope I get a shower and white bedsheets tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.47,0:05:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I'm tired of campfires and camping out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.77,0:06:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, whatever happens, happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.96,0:06:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(580, 350)\frz8\fry340\fs18}Welcome Inside
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.96,0:06:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(575, 380)\frz6\fry330\fs20}Coffee - Snacks
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.72,0:06:29.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's all the stink?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.76,0:06:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like an abandoned roadside restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.60,0:06:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess this is handy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.10,0:06:39.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Better than camping out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.27,0:06:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, great-grandmother...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.48,0:06:42.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.02,0:06:43.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About great-grandfather...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.44,0:06:47.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.19,0:06:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maroko, let him out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.82,0:06:50.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.08,0:06:59.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's pitch black, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.87,0:07:01.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Find the circuit breaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.83,0:07:04.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There should be one around.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.09,0:07:05.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.25,0:07:09.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm, is this it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.06,0:07:20.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my, this is quite nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.68,0:07:24.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That settles the question of where we're staying tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.15,0:07:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's start getting ready for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.73,0:07:27.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maroko.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.69,0:07:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.82,0:07:35.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I have something to drink before dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.66,0:07:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, great-grandmother, right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.17,0:07:47.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.17,0:07:47.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(325, 350)}The third wheel
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.17,0:07:47.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(325, 395)}is a bonus
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.71,0:07:49.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you hungry? Or are you cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.84,0:07:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inumaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.05,0:07:54.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We shoplifted a fur coat three days ago, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.80,0:07:56.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.35,0:08:01.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We left that behind at the restaurant last night,\Nwhen we didn't pay for our food.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.60,0:08:04.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about that tiger-fur floor mat?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.98,0:08:07.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one we snatched from an empty home two days ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.36,0:08:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was infested with bugs, so I got rid of it this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.15,0:08:14.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got rid of it? Where?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.41,0:08:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.82,0:08:17.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't throw away a showy piece like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.70,0:08:19.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if they find us as a result?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.54,0:08:21.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be more careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.45,0:08:22.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.71,0:08:25.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh, saying "okay" is all she's good at.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.08,0:08:27.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.71,0:08:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.92,0:08:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a total shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.50,0:08:32.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.59,0:08:36.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm crying from shame!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.97,0:08:44.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been two months since we fled from Oarai Beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.27,0:08:47.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Living as fugitives, moving from town\Nto town, is not what I wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.73,0:08:52.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I could bear it, waiting for the day of recovery,\Nas long as the family stayed together.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.53,0:08:53.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.53,0:08:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every day, we shoplift;
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.82,0:08:56.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,every day, we pick pockets;
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.07,0:08:57.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,every day, we steal;
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.49,0:08:59.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,every day, we eat without paying!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.66,0:09:05.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By now, our son lnumaru is a pro shoplifter who\Nshows splendid teamwork with Maroko.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.33,0:09:09.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you! You don't reprimand him about his crimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.13,0:09:11.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You lead the way, waIking straight\Ndown the path of a criminal!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.09,0:09:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can I not cry about this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.51,0:09:19.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This wouldn't be happening if\NI'd turned myself in back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.89,0:09:22.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But just because I didn't want to part with my family...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.60,0:09:26.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, just because I didn't want to part with Maroko...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.48,0:09:31.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you turn me in back then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.15,0:09:36.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I wouldn't have experienced this\Npathetic descent into corruption.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.15,0:09:40.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could the Yomota family turn into\Na family of thieves in my generation?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.45,0:09:42.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How shameful for the rest of the family!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.49,0:09:45.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can I apologize to my ancestors!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.83,0:09:53.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you at least listen to what I have to say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.21,0:09:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough already!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.55,0:10:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the family and the parents are old, one does\Nnot get to pick and choose how to make a living.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.64,0:10:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inumaru is doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.35,0:10:11.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.86,0:10:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I honestly didn't think he had the skills for living.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.90,0:10:23.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you the least concerned that your\Nown son has turned into a criminal?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.53,0:10:28.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what were you doing when he hurt someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.66,0:10:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that was to protect Maroko...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.29,0:10:35.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The use of violence was justified to protect the family,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.17,0:10:40.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just as you robbed financial institutions\Nin order to get them back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.43,0:10:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How is that any different from the\Nillegal measures we are using,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.68,0:10:46.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,including shoplifting and dining without paying,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.72,0:10:48.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to secure the safety of the family?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.14,0:10:53.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And let me clarify one point.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.02,0:10:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I value the family bond greatly,\Nand the family life built by its members,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.74,0:11:05.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I have no interest in the family name,\Nancestors, bloodlines and such.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.37,0:11:11.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I feel great hatred for those concepts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.96,0:11:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There must be a rigid distinction between the destruction\Nof the family in the name of the law,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.55,0:11:20.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the destruction of the family,\Nfunctioning under its own bond!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.22,0:11:26.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the Yomota Family, as we exist in society,\Nis labeled as criminals by the law,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.10,0:11:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and even if we suffer untold oppression,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.18,0:11:30.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we will stay united and endure the persecution,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.56,0:11:34.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and continue to function as a family!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.61,0:11:39.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Glory to the ideal of the Yomota Family!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.96,0:11:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go, great-grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.83,0:11:58.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My, that's a darling apron.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.63,0:12:02.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great-grandmother, we came up with an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.47,0:12:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For tonight, grandfather will be the bar master,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.14,0:12:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I will be the waitress.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.01,0:12:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We want to invite you and great-grandfather\Nto our restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.81,0:12:15.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a fabulous idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.27,0:12:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.56,0:12:25.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Âut at least it gives me peace in my heart to see that\Nyou've accepted Maroko as part of our family.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.49,0:12:26.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Tamiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.87,0:12:27.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have my gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.49,0:12:35.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A family has no future unless it can accept\Na stranger, even an uninvited guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.54,0:12:43.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To be called "mother" by a strange\Ngirl accompanying her son...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.13,0:12:46.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the fate of every mother\Nwho has ever given birth to a son.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.81,0:12:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Wh-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.48,0:12:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maroko isn't Inumaru's bride!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.60,0:12:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's his granddaughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.77,0:12:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's our great-granddaughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.06,0:13:01.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what her true identity is,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.57,0:13:05.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if we have to accept her as a member of this family,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.74,0:13:10.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it makes no difference if she is my daughter\Nor my great-granddaughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.53,0:13:13.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's an issue to which time will provide the solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.00,0:13:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the child that she bears will be,\Nwithout a doubt, our grandchild.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.13,0:13:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.38,0:13:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.92,0:13:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.09,0:13:25.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you believe that it won't happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.43,0:13:30.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm finally starting to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.14,0:13:34.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What we have is a story that has gone far beyond\Nany signposts of reality and common sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.89,0:13:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a drama that embraces
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.69,0:13:44.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,risky topics about a family whose members call each\Nother parent, son, grandchild, great-grandchild.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.48,0:13:47.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can see how this will end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.41,0:13:53.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that we've come this far, we'll have\Nto stay with this rotten story to its end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.91,0:13:57.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"A grandchild who came to visit you from\Nthe near future in a time machine."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.66,0:14:02.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have the duty to follow it up, since you didn't\Neven question an unbelievable story like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.50,0:14:07.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You deserve this retribution.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.72,0:14:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on now, that's enough big talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.76,0:14:17.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go to the shopping district.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.18,0:14:18.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shuddup!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.85,0:14:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And how long do you intend to stay\Nin another family's drama?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.90,0:14:26.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can stay with it precisely because\Nit's another family's drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.32,0:14:29.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And besides, it's my duty to find the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.95,0:14:32.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or should I say, that's my role in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.82,0:14:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.49,0:14:35.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.79,0:14:42.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth that this fictitious family might still carry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.84,0:14:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Detectives Do Not Believe In Love"\NSinger / Tatara Bannai : Yomota Tamiko
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.30,0:14:59.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Love is a sin", spoken by rosy lips.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.14,0:15:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The present you see with your black eyes is all a deception.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.52,0:15:14.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My life is that of a hidden cameraman, always hiding,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.95,0:15:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,covered by telephoto lenses and thoughts of exposure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.67,0:15:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(Click, click)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.09,0:15:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All men
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.38,0:15:34.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(Click, click)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.30,0:15:38.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,dream about their lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.72,0:15:41.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(Click, click)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.64,0:15:46.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All women
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.65,0:15:49.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(Click, click)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.23,0:15:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,turn their back on the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.99,0:16:03.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detectives do not believe in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.79,0:16:15.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this out-of-focus tomorrow an illusion?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.64,0:16:23.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The shadows within the depth of field are all from the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.06,0:16:30.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The world will one day feel like a mirage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.57,0:16:40.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is a black and white photograph.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.03,0:16:42.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(Click, click)
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.79,0:16:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All men
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.83,0:16:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(Click, click)
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.88,0:16:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,feel passion for their subjects.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.47,0:16:58.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(Click, click)
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.01,0:17:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All women
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.10,0:17:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,(Click, click)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.73,0:17:10.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,turn into flowers in those photographs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.48,0:17:17.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bet your life on one five-hundredth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.03,0:17:28.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detectives do not believe in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.67,0:17:34.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Machiko! You're super!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.80,0:17:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yamadera! You're too good with that song!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.80,0:17:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop looking down on society.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.36,0:17:57.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are two scenes that are never\Nshown on the stage called life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.03,0:18:02.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are the birth and the death of the self.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.24,0:18:04.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who could ever see them?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.37,0:18:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The memory of birth that has been long forgotten,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.91,0:18:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the moment of death that nobody is allowed to witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.58,0:18:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What people witness are always the scenes\Nof other people's births and deaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.17,0:18:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The self exists on uncertain ground,\Nsomewhere between birth and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.39,0:18:22.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is continuously exposed to anxiety,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.43,0:18:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the end of its drama is endlessly delayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.22,0:18:29.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is why people seek out stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.60,0:18:33.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For beginnings full of anticipation, and emotional finales.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.19,0:18:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For beginnings and endings.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.98,0:18:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is always a beginning and an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.24,0:18:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From the origin to the conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.28,0:18:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From alpha to omega.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.32,0:18:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A boy meets a girl;
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.20,0:18:46.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a girl separates from a boy;
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.33,0:18:49.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,once upon a time, they lived happily ever after.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.79,0:18:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People still seek them, and that\Nis why they still follow stories,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.05,0:18:57.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as kindhearted listeners,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.42,0:18:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as generous audiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.59,0:19:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unknowingly they play roles in them,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.97,0:19:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as producers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.18,0:19:05.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Full monty!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.39,0:19:11.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They occasionally avert the dullness of\Nthe story development with sly tactics
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.35,0:19:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and take the story straight towards the finale.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.11,0:19:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,'Tis a pipe dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.94,0:19:18.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,'Tis a half-credible rumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.23,0:19:20.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,'Tis an incomprehensible grumbling.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.28,0:19:25.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These are the true forms of what people know as stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.78,0:19:30.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is the format of stories that lead to their conclusions\Naccording to inevitable causation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.79,0:19:33.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The power of drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.04,0:19:38.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The beginning and end of stories of true life drama
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.63,0:19:42.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are the real stories that never cease to attract viewers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.26,0:19:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And unfortunately, people start their\Nlives amidst a vortex of stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.51,0:19:53.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, on the stage called family, which everyone experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.35,0:19:57.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how ironic it is
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.27,0:20:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that the story, which is constantly moving toward its finale,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.07,0:20:05.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,must start on the stage of blood relationships,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.41,0:20:07.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,where nobody knows when it started or when it will end.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.99,0:20:10.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.16,0:20:13.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that is the case, the ultimate theme of this story,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.04,0:20:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or, the theme of all stories ever,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.50,0:20:21.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,must be to end that story itself!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.30,0:20:25.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now this story, which started with a forceful initial premise,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.89,0:20:29.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and has gone through numerous forceful\Ndevelopments, is about to reach its finale,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.56,0:20:33.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there is no better person to put an end to it than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.06,0:20:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, me, the one who has played\Nnumerous roles throughout,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.52,0:20:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,always carrying the leitmotiv of destruction and destiny!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.86,0:20:43.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Howl, wind!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.61,0:20:45.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dash, cloud!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.49,0:20:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Raise the final curtain and put an end\Nto this supremely chaotic story!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.43,0:21:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, but we're already closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.64,0:21:15.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a pretty good ad lib, but I have no time to deal with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.77,0:21:16.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a sec!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.60,0:21:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.52,0:21:18.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.35,0:21:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said, I don't have time for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.95,0:21:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Criminals inside the roadside restaurant!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.28,0:21:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're completely surrounded!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.66,0:21:33.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Resistance is futile!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.20,0:21:35.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Surrender your weapons and come out immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.29,0:21:42.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it, how did they find out?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.75,0:21:45.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should've crossed the prefectural line tonight, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.46,0:21:46.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do, Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.34,0:21:48.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go outside and fight, or stay put?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.55,0:21:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're done for!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.35,0:21:52.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.18,0:21:56.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If things are turning out like this,\NI should've turned myself in.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.31,0:21:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.52,0:21:59.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.23,0:22:00.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.65,0:22:02.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The end has already been ordained.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.27,0:22:04.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Yomota Family is trapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.28,0:22:08.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether you turn yourself in or fight to the end,\Nyour arrest is only a matter of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.53,0:22:13.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The front page of the morning paper will\Nrecount the arrest of this criminal family.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.08,0:22:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! No! I don't want that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.16,0:22:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's actually a third choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.21,0:22:23.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only path that will protect the honor of the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.75,0:22:26.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something only {\i1}you{\i0} can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.72,0:22:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Use this and finish your dearest family in a single blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.39,0:22:32.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.60,0:22:33.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.64,0:22:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why hesitate?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.60,0:22:35.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why fear?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.85,0:22:39.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really want your family to live a life of shame?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.60,0:22:41.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they're arrested, they'll be behind\Nbars for a minimum of ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.65,0:22:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And even if the rest of the family is released early,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.94,0:22:47.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what kind of future will a family have whose\Nstrongest support is still in prison?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.69,0:22:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than let them live a life of corruption again, you can...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.03,0:22:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.70,0:22:57.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! This!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.95,0:22:59.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.25,0:23:00.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.21,0:23:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamiko! Inumaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.79,0:23:03.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maroko!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.96,0:23:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Die with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.51,0:23:10.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.97,0:23:12.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you crazy, Dad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.01,0:23:13.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you wanna die, just kill yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.34,0:23:15.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll follow right behind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.22,0:23:17.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go on ahead of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.60,0:23:20.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inumaru! Step forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.89,0:23:22.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.14,0:23:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead and shoot me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.77,0:23:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But let me tell you one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.94,0:23:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.19,0:23:28.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! A UFO!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.40,0:23:29.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where? Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.97,0:23:59.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.02,0:24:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The story of the family you've been pursuing all this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.14,0:24:09.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you want to finish it with\Nsuch an idiotic development?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.90,0:24:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A truly great ending must always be executed as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.66,0:24:16.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything foreshadowed this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.16,0:24:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a man who has been mentioned before\Nbut has never appeared on screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.12,0:24:29.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is the last character of the story and is supposed\Nto turn things around completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.71,0:24:31.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.55,0:24:33.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm him, Maroko.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.34,0:24:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.14,0:24:51.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My actions were not intended to carry\Nout my duty as a time patroller.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.44,0:24:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were to prevent you from seeing your ancestors,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.07,0:24:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,especially that man, who is my father and your grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.91,0:25:00.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.28,0:25:03.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why must I {\i1}not{\i0} see my grandfather?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.12,0:25:13.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've rarely spoken to you about my\Nmother - about your grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.46,0:25:15.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard she was very unique.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.92,0:25:19.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather Inumaru has not met that woman yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.76,0:25:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He met her long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.26,0:25:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the beginning of this story.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.02,0:25:29.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those who knew my mother said
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.44,0:25:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that she appeared one day like the wind,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.44,0:25:34.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,brought chaos and destruction to the Yomota family,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.15,0:25:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,gave birth to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.07,0:25:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and abruptly disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.53,0:25:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was like a traveler who visited this land\Nfrom a distant place and then returned home.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.33,0:25:50.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her name was finally identified the year after you were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.75,0:25:53.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a sad revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.34,0:25:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feared my own deduction,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.09,0:25:59.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and feared my deduction would become reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.89,0:26:03.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I enlisted with the Time Patrol to\Nprevent the very day I feared.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.31,0:26:12.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Yomota Inumaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.77,0:26:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father's name is Inumaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.32,0:26:16.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father's father's name is Kinekuni.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.19,0:26:19.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And my mother's name is Yomota Maroko.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.57,0:26:22.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A pleasure to meet you, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.58,0:26:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm your son, Inumaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.75,0:26:39.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Day after day on that deserted beach, I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.55,0:26:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as a father who was born from his own daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.68,0:26:45.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as a son who raised his own mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.76,0:26:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about where would be the best place to\Nend this cursed cycle of blood relations.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.98,0:26:57.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.90,0:26:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, Maroko.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.61,0:27:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.45,0:27:08.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you tell me one thing before I pull the trigger?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.00,0:27:16.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you conceived me yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.22,0:27:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is where it all ends, leaving one last mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.47,0:27:32.81,Gosenzo,,0000,0000,0000,,Long live the ancestors!
